|body2= '''[Dr. Stygian's Annotation]'''

This was Elias' last words before he turned. I wish it could have been better for him but he had it coming for him.


I have been at this station for fourteen months. I have four hundred and sixty reports. I have reviewed them all and 
I have revised my conclusions three times and I am revising them again.


The Hollows are patient. I have been thinking of patience as a property of predators — the stillness of 
something that is waiting to be approached.
I am beginning to think patience might be something else here. I am beginning to think it might be grief.


I do not know what to do with that. I am writing it down because writing things down is what I do here and 
because if I am wrong there is no harm in having written it and if I am right then someone should have written it.


Something lived here. It built here. It existed here in sufficient density to leave a shape behind. And 
then whatever gave it life was taken away, or consumed, or chose to leave, and what remained was the outline 
of it. The shape with nothing inside.}}
